    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-07-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="310"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Señor
                            <persName type="to">Lazcano</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-07-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 21, 1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In compliance with the request contained in your
                    note of the 18th instant, I have the honor to inclose certified copies of your
                    note of the 4th instant and of the telegram of May 8 last from our consul at
                    Valparaiso, both relating to the ownership of the <hi rend="italic"
                    >Itata</hi>.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William F. Wharton</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
